  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: this is the issue @Chad noticed during test session and it is clearly visible on my iPhone 5S: when I pull down the screen to refresh (transaction history or main wallet) it is not smooth and I can see 2 spinners sometimes for a second as well as the UI itself hangs for a second. TF does not show it perfectly but if you try to do it on real device i believe you will see it too (if even iPhone X has this issue) .\r\nI can also reproduce it (but in not so obvious way) on iPhone 7.\r\n\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28752642/34342229-1c2e1cf2-e9ba-11e7-98d0-5240f0b943c0.png)\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28752642/34342276-d4a7cd9a-e9bb-11e7-9ecb-1b7e6499e29b.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nNOTE: looks much better on Android\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nI can refresh history and list of assets by `pull-to-refresh` gesture smoothly\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Go to Wallet and Refresh\r\n- Go to transaction history and refresh\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: develop\r\n* Operating System: iOS\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\nTF iPhone 5S: https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803590-status/builds/7370858/sessions/10/?accessToken=gL2WTmOk1G1f06ABpXDAOoErePE\r\n\r\nTF iPhone 7: https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803590-status/builds/7371255/sessions/1/?accessToken=NDKe/Xv8yMw5r5CCGCcx0QkiDQk",
